	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.60]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Another option is just to allow them to trade items they can get, of equivalent value. When I need pelts for tailoring, I go to ec, and offer to make banded armor in exchange for pelts, same rates I usually pay 1pp for LQ, 2 for MQ, 3 for HQ, except bear which is 40pp. Calculate banded at 1pp per ac and swap. Also take spider/spiderling silks the same way. Works out cheaper for me, since the banded doesn't cost 1pp per ac to make, and the lowbies seem to like getting armor instead of cash. Saves them the time of turning around and auctioning to buy the armor after they get the cash. Could do the same with weapons, etc. that you loot. <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
